name: WSJ
text: A group of prominent actors, writers and producers are protesting NBC News’s decision to carry a town hall meeting with President Trump opposite the previously scheduled Joe Biden town hall on rival ABC News https://t.co/hciWPlX8wU

name: WSJ
text: See a guide to where President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden stand on policy issues including job creation and wages, policing and racial injustice and student debt and college costs https://t.co/1yAj8SGLhn

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: President Trump said he didn’t know whether he took a Covid-19 test on the day of the presidential debate, saying "Possibly I did, possibly I didn’t." He added his doctors told him his lungs were infected, but declined to offer specifics. https://t.co/neb09ahW0E

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: Joe Biden said that the president should put in place a national standard for pandemic response, unlike President Trump, who has mostly left it up to the states https://t.co/unQDZjJ9BG

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: President Trump dodged a request that he denounce the conspiracy-theory group known as QAnon during a contentious NBC town hall meeting, saying, “I know nothing about QAnon,” and adding, “I do know they are very much against pedophelia." https://t.co/taLvaByNXR

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: Asked if he might seek a delay in seeking his tax increases on corporations and the wealthiest Americans as the economy recovers from the coronavirus, Biden, who served in the Senate, was blunt about his prospects: “I gotta get the votes” https://t.co/6lyCED64xr

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: President Trump equivocated on the importance of wearing masks to prevent the spread of Covid-19, citing without evidence a statistic about people who use face coverings getting the illness and then advocating for wearing masks https://t.co/RKapyX70XN

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: Joe Biden said it was a mistake to support the 1994 crime law that led to an increase in incarceration of Black men https://t.co/LwyZ1nc1TD

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: President Trump insisted Senate Republicans will back him on a stimulus deal despite their current misgivings about the price tag of the potential $2 trillion package https://t.co/vq6WwquopB

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: Joe Biden said he intends to announce his position on overhauling the Supreme Court before the election—depending on how the Senate handles the nomination of Judge Amy Coney Barrett https://t.co/QWY9HKhaSZ

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: President Trump repeatedly declined to say whether he would like to see Roe v. Wade, the landmark decision establishing abortion rights, overturned by the Supreme Court https://t.co/08qGwMbvUM

name: WSJ
text: Live analysis: Joe Biden complimented President Trump on a recent Middle East accord his administration announced, but he also said the U.S. was more isolated and less secure under Trump's leadership: "We're not very well trusted around the world" https://t.co/PgYAS2pFR3

name: WSJ
text: Analysis: The town halls with President Trump and Joe Biden were markedly different in style and tone, with the president repeatedly locked in tense exchanges with the host while his rival engaged in more calm back and forth. Here were some top moments. https://t.co/biuEtfa4d0

name: WSJ
text: An under-the-radar tech billionaire who happens to own the Memphis Grizzlies is piecing together an impressive portfolio of private homes from New York to Seattle https://t.co/piMD63ZSVZ

name: WSJ
text: Republican Sen. Ben Sasse criticized President Trump’s record and ethics in a call with constituents, marking the sharpest break with the president by a GOP senator during the campaign so far https://t.co/lqzsgEqg4K

name: WSJ
text: From @WSJopinion: President Trump was more focused than usual at Monday’s rally, dwelling on differences over tax cuts, China, energy and the Supreme Court. He needs that discipline to win, writes @KarlRove. https://t.co/3eLvYrpT4a

text: The pandemic made toilet paper and disinfectant wipes scarce. Now canned corn is the latest hard-to-find item at the grocery store. https://t.co/o1H2g2G8vV

text: Gen. Salvador Cienfuegos, Mexico’s former defense minister, was arrested in Los Angeles at the request of the DEA, senior Mexican officials said. He is the highest ranking Mexican official to be arrested in connection with drug-related corruption. https://t.co/HkvH9nudOM

text: Twitter’s legal and policy chief said the company would change how it enforces certain content rules, citing “significant feedback” on how it handled recent articles from the New York Post https://t.co/8M5QSu8b7T
